    "closed_at": null,
    "body": "**This is not a bug of NPM but a limitation of how `$PATH` works. Leave this note to let others to avoid spending time on it ðŸ˜„** Probably better to put this in wiki, but I do not have permission to edit wiki pages.\r\n\r\n* `npm run` add absolute path of `node_modules/.bin` to `$PATH`.\r\n* `$PATH` uses colon (`:`) as separator\r\n* It is possible to put `:` in a directory name\r\n\r\nAs a result, if absolute path of your `node_modules/.bin` contains `:` somewhere, `npm run x` can fail if it uses executable in the `node_modules/.bin`.  For example, if you use `gulp` then it will show an error: `sh: gulp: command not found`.\r\n\r\nTo avoid this problem, do not use colon (`:`) in directory name.\r\n\r\nNote: if you're using Mac, if you create a new directory with slash in Finder, it is shown as `:` in command line although you see `/` in Finder."
