    "body": "We get tons of ECONNRESET errors on our build servers. Tracking down why the errors happen has been a real headscratcher.\r\n\r\nIdeally, any time NPM encounters an ECONNRESET or an ETIMEOUT error, it should display whatever URL it was attempting to grab which triggered the error. Otherwise, the existing error logs don't provide many clues:\r\n\r\n```\r\n[23:03:34][npm install] npm ERR! node v4.2.4\r\n[23:03:34][npm install] npm ERR! npm  v3.9.6\r\n[23:03:34][npm install] npm ERR! code ECONNRESET\r\n[23:03:34][npm install] npm ERR! errno ECONNRESET\r\n[23:03:34][npm install] npm ERR! syscall read\r\n[23:03:34][npm install] \r\n[23:03:34][npm install] npm ERR! network read ECONNRESET\r\n[23:03:34][npm install] npm ERR! network This is most likely not a problem with npm itself\r\n[23:03:34][npm install] npm ERR! network and is related to network connectivity.\r\n[23:03:34][npm install] npm ERR! network In most cases you are behind a proxy or have bad network settings.\r\n[23:03:34][npm install] npm ERR! network \r\n[23:03:34][npm install] npm ERR! network If you are behind a proxy, please make sure that the\r\n[23:03:34][npm install] npm ERR! network 'proxy' config is set properly.  See: 'npm help config'\r\n[23:03:35][npm install] npm ERR! Linux 4.4.2\r\n[23:03:35][npm install] npm ERR! argv \"/var/teamcity/build-agent/system/asdf/v4.2.4/bin/node\" \"/var/teamcity/build-agent/system/asdf/v4.2.4/bin/npm\" \"install\"\r\n[23:03:35][npm install] npm ERR! node v4.2.4\r\n[23:03:35][npm install] npm ERR! npm  v3.9.6\r\n[23:03:35][npm install] npm ERR! code ECONNRESET\r\n[23:03:35][npm install] npm ERR! errno ECONNRESET\r\n[23:03:35][npm install] npm ERR! syscall read\r\n[23:03:35][npm install] \r\n[23:03:35][npm install] npm ERR! network read ECONNRESET\r\n[23:03:35][npm install] npm ERR! network This is most likely not a problem with npm itself\r\n[23:03:35][npm install] npm ERR! network and is related to network connectivity.\r\n[23:03:35][npm install] npm ERR! network In most cases you are behind a proxy or have bad network settings.\r\n[23:03:35][npm install] npm ERR! network \r\n[23:03:35][npm install] npm ERR! network If you are behind a proxy, please make sure that the\r\n[23:03:35][npm install] npm ERR! network 'proxy' config is set properly.  See: 'npm help config'\r\n[23:03:36][npm install] npm ERR! Linux 4.4.2\r\n[23:03:36][npm install] npm ERR! argv \"/var/teamcity/build-agent/system/asdf/v4.2.4/bin/node\" \"/var/teamcity/build-agent/system/asdf/v4.2.4/bin/npm\" \"install\"\r\n```"
